A minimalistic Japanese zen garden viewed from above, featuring perfectly raked white sand with precise curved lines flowing around three dark volcanic stones of varying sizes. A single delicate cherry blossom branch extends into the frame from one corner, dropping exactly five pink petals onto the sand. The composition is asymmetrical yet perfectly balanced, with vast empty space intentionally left unfilled. Soft morning light casts subtle shadows from the stones. The scene embodies purposeful simplicity where every element serves a function and nothing is superfluous.
